message: classification errors
Class described as full-size, though dimensions are much closer to rivals described as executive cars.

Full size, not midsize. May be smaller than other full sized SUVs, but it larger than the Land cruiser prado which is also a full sized, though it is similar in size to the discovery and defender, which are both midsized. The LWB however is definately full sized.
The dimensions similar to other executive cars show that this is not a full-sized vehicle. Much like the Taycan and e-tron GT, this is an E segment car.
Q7 is a mid size SUV, not Full size. Audi's upcoming Q9 SUV has been spotted. That is full-size, not this one. Q7 rivals the GLE and X5. Q9 will rival the GLS and X7.
FOR THE LAST TIME, STOP REVERTING EDITS FROM PEOPLE WHO KNOW A LOT ABOUT CARS
Looks like you don't care that other editors on here disagree with the classification. Many sources say it's full-size.
